5/ I just started using it today so haven't taken full advantage of Alchemy's tools yet. 

But another benefit is that you can see your transactions in the mempool (that's where transactions chill while waiting to get picked up by miners).

4/ You can do this in three steps

1. Create an Alchemy Account
2. Create a new app in Alchemy
3. Add a custom RPC to MM using the app's endpoint

This article will walk you through it step-by-step: https://t.co/HWVzwpHbqJ

3/ Alchemy gives you your own custom endpoint. One primary benefit is that your transactions get picked up much faster since you're dealing w/ less competition.

I timed my transactions to see the difference in speed:
â€¢ Default RPC: 41.34 seconds
â€¢ Alchemy RPC: 25.81 seconds
2/ M*taM*sk uses a default node provider using Infura as its endpoint. That means everyone else using MM *also* has this as their default node provider.
